1. *Loša* vest je stigla iz bolnice. (*Loša* - adjective, subject complement) - The bad news arrived from the hospital.

2. Ona *loše* govori engleski jezik. (*Loše* - adverb, modifying verb) - She speaks English badly.

3. Ne bih želeo da mi se *loše* desi. (*Loše* - adverb, modifying verb) - I wouldn't want something bad to happen to me.

4. *Loši* uslovi rada dovode do lošeg kvaliteta proizvoda. (*Loši* - adjective, modifying noun) - Poor working conditions lead to poor product quality.

5. Kada je *loš* učenik, treba mu pružiti pomoć. (*Loš* - adjective, modifying noun) - When a student is bad, they need help.

6. Moja majka pravi *loše* kolače. (*Loše* - adverb, modifying verb) - My mother bakes cakes badly.

7. Oni su veoma *loši* ljudi. (*Loši* - adjective, modifying noun) - They are very bad people.

8. Nije dobro što *loša* vest dolazi kasno. (*Loša* - adjective, modifying noun) - It's not good that the bad news is coming late.

9. Da li se osećaš *loše*? (*Loše* - adverb, modifying verb) - Do you feel bad?

10. Koliko često praviš *loše* odluke? (*Loše* - adverb, modifying verb) - How often do you make bad decisions?